    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-ml-hemolysis-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-cv-sim-lab-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per the MRL 2 requirements matrix. The ML surrogate demonstrates strong agreement with experimental hemolysis measurements (max deviation 4.7%) and correctly identifies the worst-case operating condition. Validation metrics from the single training run are considered sufficient for the Medium model influence and High decision consequence combination at MRL 2. The assessment team noted informally that retraining produced similar results, and no further characterization of training-seed variance was deemed necessary for this submission.",
